Defendant Chester L Fisher in court with attorney Reyna Ivonne Morales.  Abbey Marie DeSiato appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by counsel, the defendant and the Court.  AS TO COUNTS 1 & 2:  Court sentenced defendant to serve 6 MONTHS in the House of Correction, EACH COUNT, consecutive to each other and any other sentence. STRAIGHT TIME; credit for 1 day served as to Count 1.  Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 15 MONTHS with the following conditions:
- As a condition of probation, the Court ordered the defendant to serve 40 days in the House of Correction as to each count.  This time is stayed pending review hearing.
- Attend and successfully complete Batterers Intervention Program.
- Attend the following programs and/or assessments:  Parenting Class.
- Attend treatment and counseling programs as determined by agent.
- Maintain absolute sobriety.
- No violent contact with AEF (dob:  2/8/2007).
- Cooperate with Bureau of Milwaukee Child Welfare.
- No physical disciplinie.
- Obtain/maintain employment.
- No contact with firearms.
- Court ordered probation may terminate early if defendant has completed all programs and paid all fees.
- Court WAIVED supervision fees based on inability to pay, except shall pay 2 DNA surcharges and mandatory costs, fees and surcharges.
- Court advised defendant of his right to seek postconviction relief.  Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.  Court ordered case adjourned for probation review hearing in Branch 23.  Probation Review Hearing scheduled for 01-16-2015 at 01:30 pm.

AS TO AMENDED COUNTS 1 & 2
Defendant changes plea(s) to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to plea, advised of Constitutional Rights and the maximum penalties. Court found that the defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived rights.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights form, received and filed. Parties stipulate to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea(s).  Court found defendant GUILTY and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Court advised defendant of penalties for violation of NO CONTACT ORDER. Court advised that under 48 USC Section 922(g)(9) the defendant is prohibited from possession of a firearm and/or ammunition after conviction of a misdemeanor crime of domestic violence. Case adjourned to branch 23 for Sentencing.

Defendant Chester L Fisher in court with attorney Reyna Ivonne Morales.  Matthew J. Torbenson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case set for Jury Trial. Parties have reached a resolution in this matter. 
AS TO COUNT 1
Pursuant to plea negotiations, on a motion of the state, the court ordered Count 1 Amended to : 
- - COUNT 1: Misdemeanor Battery, contrary to Wis. Stat. 940.19(1), a class A Misdemeanor.
- - COUNT 2: Misdemeanor Battery, contrary to Wis. Stat. 940.19(1), a class A Misdemeanor.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for August 22, 2014 at 08:30 am.
